race.comment: MR ENCORE (1) loves it here around this circuit with four wins and a second from just six starts and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Looks the one they all have to run down. BOLD TEE (2) looked good on debut saluting at Ipswich before being too bad to be true at Beaudesert. Has since been given further time to mature and a strong showing while fresh would not surprise. BEITSOO (6) has a win and two seconds from six attempts over this track and trip and will strip fitter second-up from the spell. Top-three conveyance. LEVAR (3) just ran into one better over this course and distance last time out and has been racing very consistently of late. In the mix. BLERIOT (5) goes well for hoop Robbins who has three wins and three placings from nine steers. Don't underestimate.
